<blockquote>
<p dir="auto">Note that the elements of <code>hiddenChildren</code> will, if later <a href="#api">revealed</a>, have
their <code>position</code> data stripped off using <a href="https://github.com/syntax-tree/unist-util-remove-position">unist-util-remove-position</a>
(making them <a href="https://github.com/syntax-tree/unist#generated">generated nodes</a>). This is because <code>position</code> data can be
invalidated at any time due to it being <a href="https://github.com/remarkjs/remark-gfm/issues/16#issuecomment-841200438" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/remarkjs/remark-gfm/issues/16/hovercard">impossible</a> to know how later
plugins will manipulate the AST. Missing <code>position</code> data will not crash any
remark plugins that properly follow the <a href="https://github.com/syntax-tree/unist#node">unist spec</a>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p dir="auto">And running the following JavaScript:</p>
